# Orchestrator: UX Flow Designer workflow

For every user-facing feature, invoke `ux-flow-designer` after the feature contract architect has created the initial architecture contract and before implementation workers start.

## Required ordering

1. `feature-contract-architect` — produces contracts, vocabulary, packages
2. **`ux-flow-designer`** — produces UX flow contract (`docs/features/<name>/09-ux-flow-contract.md`)
3. Architect updates vertical work packages so each implementation worker receives:
   - technical contract
   - UX contract
   - allowed files
   - forbidden files
   - screen/state requirements
   - acceptance criteria
4. `implementation-worker` subagents — implement slices
5. `test-writer` subagents — write tests per contract
6. `reviewer` subagent — checks contract compliance

## Hard rule

Implementation workers must not invent UI flows, layouts, labels, or states not defined in the UX contract.

## UX contract location

```
docs/features/<feature-name>/09-ux-flow-contract.md
```